## Error: Can't coerce element 1 from a double to a logical
z_score = function(x) {
  
  if (!is.numeric(x)) {
    stop("argument x should be numeric")
  } else if (length(x) == 1) {
    stop("z-scores cannot be computed for length 1 vectors")
  }
  
  mean_x = mean(x)
  sd_x = sd(x)
  z = mean_x / sd_x
  
  data_frame(
    mean = mean_x, 
    sd = sd_x,
    z = z
  )
}

library(stringr)

read_page_reviews <- function(url) {
  
  h = read_html(url)
  
  title = h %>%
    html_nodes("#cm_cr-review_list .review-title") %>%
    html_text()
  
  stars = h %>%
    html_nodes("#cm_cr-review_list .review-rating") %>%
    html_text() %>%
    str_extract("\\d") %>%
    as.numeric()
  
  text = h %>%
    html_nodes(".review-data:nth-child(4)") %>%
    html_text()
  
  data_frame(title, stars, text)
}

Simulation

Simulations!! YES!!

one n

SLR function:

sim_regression = function(n, beta0, beta1) {
  
  sim_data = tibble(
    x = rnorm(n, mean = 1, sd = 1),
    y = beta0 + beta1 * x + rnorm(n, 0, 1)
  )
  
  ls_fit = lm(y ~ x, data = sim_data)
  
  tibble(
    n = n,
    beta0_hat = coef(ls_fit)[1],
    beta1_hat = coef(ls_fit)[2]
  )
}
sim_regression(30, 2, 3)
## # A tibble: 1 x 3
##       n beta0_hat beta1_hat
##   <dbl>     <dbl>     <dbl>
## 1    30  1.718911  3.080536

Use a for loop …

output = vector("list", 100)

for (i in 1:100) {
  
  output[[i]] = sim_regression(30, 2, 3)
  
}

sim_results = output %>% 
  bind_rows()
sim_results = rerun(100, sim_regression(30, 2, 3)) %>% 
  bind_rows()

Clear as mud!!

sim_results %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = beta0_hat)) + geom_density()

sim_results %>% 
  gather(key = parameter, value = estimate, beta0_hat:beta1_hat) %>% 
  group_by(parameter) %>% 
  summarize(emp_mean = mean(estimate),
            emp_var = var(estimate)) %>% 
  knitr::kable(digits = 3)

replace for with a map

simulate_n = function(n_rep, n_samp, beta0, beta1) {
  
  rerun(n_rep, sim_regression(n_samp, beta0, beta1)) %>% 
    bind_rows()
  
}

sim_results = map(n_samp, simulate_n,
                  n_rep = 1000, beta0 = 2, beta1 = 3)

sim_results = sim_results %>% 
  bind_rows
relabel_function = function(n) { str_c("n = ", n) }

sim_results %>% 
  mutate(n = as.factor(n),
         n = fct_relabel(n, relabel_function)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = n, y = beta1_hat, fill = n)) + 
  geom_violin()

sim_results %>% 
  mutate(n = as.factor(n),
         n = fct_relabel(n, relabel_function)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = beta0_hat, y = beta1_hat)) + 
  geom_point(alpha = .2) + 
  facet_grid(~n)
